The frequency of each element in the list is stored in a hashmap, where each element is a pair (name, age), and the key is the name. You then loop through each entry in the hashmap, and for each pair, find the corresponding age value in the list. This will allow you to count the number of penguins less than 8 years old.

Here is the pseudocode:

// Create a hashmap to store the frequency of each element
Map<String, Integer> frequencyMap = new Map<String, Integer>();

// Loop through the list of penguins
for (Penguin penguin : penguins) {
   // Find the corresponding age value in the list
   int age = penguin.age;

   // Add the age value to the frequency map
   frequencyMap.put(penguin.name, frequencyMap.get(penguin.name) + 1);
}

// Find the number of penguins less than 8 years old
int count = 0;
for (String name : frequencyMap.keys()) {
   if (frequencyMap.get(name) < 8) {
      count++;
   }
}

// Return the number of penguins less than 8 years old
return count;

